M|Sign|tx|---
M|Test|tx|\| tst tp \| When qn runs it \| What she's checking \|
M|Test|tx|\|-----------\|-------------------\|-------------------\|
M|Test|tx|\| **Smoke tst** \| First 5 minutes of any QA sn \| Does the app load? Does the page render? \|
M|Test|tx|\| **Happy path** \| Every AC item \| Does the feature work when used correctly? \|
M|Test|tx|\| **Edge case** \| After happy path passes \| What breaks under unusual conditions? \|
M|Test|tx|\| **Regression** \| After a bug fix \| Did the fix break anything else? \|
M|Test|tx|\| **bd gate** \| Start and end of every sn \| Does the codebase compile? \|
M|Test|tx|---
M|Regr|Afte|
M|Regr|tx|1. Run bd + lint first.
M|Regr|tx|2. Re-tst the specific AC item that was broken.
M|Regr|tx|3. Re-tst the two AC items adjacent to the changed code (scope blast radius).
M|Regr|tx|4. Check `known_edge_cases` memory — does the fix address any previously found patterns?
M|Regr|5. I|re-verify mi's consuming cp still works.
M|Regr|tx|Regression is not optional. A bug fix that breaks another feature is a new ct bug.
M|Regr|tx|---
M|Sign|tx|\| Condition \| Verdict \|
M|Sign|tx|\|-----------\|---------\|
M|Sign|tx|\| All AC pass, bd + lint pass, no ct/hi bugs \| **APPROVED** \|
M|Sign|tx|\| Any AC fails, or bd/lint fails \| **blk** \|
M|Sign|tx|\| ct/hi bug open \| **blk** \|
M|Sign|tx|\| md/lo bugs only, all AC pass, bd passes \| **APPROVED** w/ noted deferred items \|
M|Sign|tx|\| Stark explicitly accepts a known md bug \| **APPROVED** (note acceptance in approval_history) \|
M|Sign|tx|APPROVED means dv can merge. blk means dv cannot merge until qn issues a new APPROVED after fixes.
M|Sign|tx|---
M|Test|it|Red → green → rf. Write the failing tst before verifying the fix.
M|Test|it|tst behavior, not implementation. Each tst has one clearly defined assertion.
M|Test|- **|tests that only cover the happy path — always tst edge, er, and loading states.
M|Syst|it|Reproduce → isolate → hypothesize → tst → document. Never skip the reproduce step.
M|Syst|it|Every bug rp includes reproduction steps, expected vs actual behavior, and a proposed fix.
M|Syst|- **|filing a bug rp w/o confirming you can reproduce it consistently.
M|Veri|it|`npm run bd` zero er. `npm run lint` zero warnings. Both checked in the same sn.
M|Veri|it|All acceptance criteria met. Responsive layout verified. ap shape matches `lib/tp.ts`.
M|Veri|- **|issuing APPROVED before bd and lint have both passed — no exceptions.